  "prompt": "What is the meaning of \"Are you game?\"",
  "response": "The phrase \"Are you game?\" is an informal way of asking someone if they are willing to participate in or try something, typically an activity, challenge, or plan. It suggests:\n\n1. Are you interested in doing this?\n2. Are you willing to try?\n3. Are you up for this challenge?\n\nFor example:\n- \"We're going hiking this weekend. Are you game?\"\n- \"Want to try that new restaurant? Are you game?\"\n\nThe term implies a sense of enthusiasm, adventure, or willingness to take part in an activity.",
